  "title": "Receptionist (Law Firm)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Greet clients and visitors with warmth and professionalism.</li><li>Answer and direct phone calls, take messages, and handle general enquiries.</li><li>Manage appointment scheduling and meeting room arrangements.</li><li>Receive, sort, and distribute mail and courier deliveries.</li><li>Maintain the reception area and ensure it is tidy and welcoming.</li><li>Assist in preparing and organizing documents for meetings.</li><li>Provide administrative support to lawyers and office staff as required.</li><li>Handle confidential information with discretion and accuracy.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>GCE ‘O’ Level, Diploma, or equivalent qualification.</li><li>prior experience is NOT required. Training will be provided.</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Professional appearance, pleasant personality, and service-oriented attitude.</li><li>Strong organizational skills with attention to detail.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Outlook).</li><li>Ability to multitask and work independently in a fast-paced environment.</li></ul>",
